3.3 Dealing with errors
=======================

 The _XSLT-process_ mode intercepts the error messages generated by
the XML parser or XSLT processor and displays them in compilation
buffer, which quickly allows you to go to the cause of the error. 
When you encounter an error, just click using the middle-button
(assuming an X-Windows system or suitable three-button emulation) on
the error message. Emacs will move the cursor point at the place that
caused the error. If you only have a two-button mouse you should can
emulate the third button using the operating system (Linux) or Emacs
(Windows) (see *Note Convenience Settings::).  


