7 Future enhancements
*********************

 This is a list of features planned for future releases. The list
doesn't specify any particular order in the priority, and the
features may or may not be implemented. 
     

   * Add the ability to evaluate XPath expressions. The context node
     could be either the top node of the XML document or it can be
     specified by putting the point on it.  This would be a very
     useful tool for novice XSLT users to learn XPath (and Emacs ;-).
     This is a non-trivial enhancement, but one of the developers
     would like to have it for teaching purposes. Until this
     enhancement is available consider using XPath Explorer (see
     `http://sourceforge.net/projects/xpe') 

   * Add the ability to go both forward and backwards in time during
     debugging. This would be a nice feature to have for the cases
     where reaching the point of interest in the stylesheet takes a
     lot of time, and the pressing the wrong key makes you miss it.
     
   


